<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 2 SPEED REAR AXLES: SPICER - ASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>ASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="1">
            <title>DIFFERENTIAL</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401520">Figure 20.</hotlnk>
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401520" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401520" filename="../figg14/G1401520.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="352px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 20. Differential Reassembly</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply a small amount of lubricant to all mating surfaces. This will keep thrust washer
                    in place during assembly, and provide for initial lubrication.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place thrust washer and side gear in left hand differential case.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Assemble differential pinions and thrust washers on cross shaft. Place assembly in left
                    side of differential case.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place side gear and thrust washer in position on differential pinions.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Assemble case halves,
                    <emph type="bold">making sure match marks are lined up.</emph>
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install case bolts. Tighten alternately and evenly. Tighten bolts to:</para>
                <para>14CDA and 14130, 70 to 80 ft-lbs. (95 to 108 N&#8226;m).</para>
            </step1>
            <para>14131, 14132, 14133 and 14CDB, 110 to 125 ft-lbs. (149 to 169 N&#8226;m).</para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
